Dear Governor Perdue,

Please oppose H1575, a special-interest bill that weakens
cleanup standards for polluted soil and groundwater.

Remediation of contaminated sites is expensive. Because it is
expensive, most companies take care to manage toxic chemicals
carefully. H1575 would let companies that cause spills walk away
without fully cleaning up their mistakes, transferring the cost
to future generations. With spills costing much less to deal
with, corporations would spend less to avoid them, leading to
more frequent spills and accidents. Please oppose H1575.


