Dear Governor Perdue,

I'm writing to ask you to oppose H1575, Accelerate Remediation
at Industrial Sites.

Current state law requires companies that spill toxic chemicals
into soil and groundwater to clean them up to background levels.
H1575 would allow companies to walk away without fully cleaning
up their pollution if they put restrictions on future land use.
But in practice, those restrictions aren't going to be enforced
or even remembered years from now, leading to future public
health problems. Please protect public health and reject H1575.


